  <summary date="2017-05-25T04:00:00Z" status="Introduced in House">Commission on Americans Living Abroad Act of 2017

This bill establishes the Commission on Americans Living Abroad which shall conduct a study of how federal laws and policies affect U.S. citizens living abroad, including civilians and members of the Armed Forces.

 Each federal agency affected by a recommendation in the report required by this bill shall submit a response to the President, Congress, and the Commission.</summary>
